  "text": "The antimicrobials might have modified the lipid monolayer structure by incorporating into the lipid monolayer, generating an aggregation of antimicrobials and lipids, thus increasing the membrane fluidity. A decreased compressibility modulus and a lift-off at larger molecular area reflect a greater intermolecular interaction between lipid and water through bridging of the natural compound at the air-water interface. Other investigators also found that some antimicrobial molecules seem to have a greater impact on the lipid molecules at the gas or liquid phases of the monolayer than at the solid phase [CITATION_1] .",
